+ How to use Marksdown

Markdown is the easiest langguage here. Because you can just type like how you write.

I will list down some effective and commonly used when you use Markdown here.You can click [Markdown](https://learnmarkdown.com/) to learn more about it.

`~~colour~~` : ~~colour~~

`  *sky*   ` : *sky*

` **sun**  ` : **sun**

` + phone  ` : + phone

` ![image name](image URL) ` : imgage will be displayed

` [link name](link URL)    ` : click on the word to direct you to the link

I really have fun learning Markdown .

### T-shirt design

There are other printing techniques

+ Inkjet printing

Use inkjet printer to print high quality image on papers and plastic substrates.
It is similar to your house printer.

+ Dye-sub printing

It is a computer printing technique that use heat to transfer images onto plastic ,card, paper or fabric.

+ Screen Printing

Use a mesh to transfer ink onto a substrate.

![screen printing](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

There are many types of printing techniques but during FabLab workshop , I learnt how to use dye-sub printing technique to print our customized designs on our t-shirt. There are 5 steps I need to follow!!!

## Step 1:Design


We can design our t-shirt on Inkscape or Canva . I then convert my images to .png or .jpg and print out.
Need to remember to click in mirror option in the computer settings.

## Step 2: Ironing

Need to iron the t shirt surface before pasting the images over the t-shirt for 5 seconds.

## Step 3: Pasting

Face the image into the t-shirt and put tape over to position the image.

## Step 4: Printing

Place the t -shirt on the heat press sublimation machine for 45seconds.Be careful on the hot surface!!
